            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_299wh' title='Col. 299WH &mdash; HC Deb 14 January 2004 vol 416 c299WH' name='column_299wh' href='#column_299wh' rel='bookmark'>299WH</a>
            know in their heart that they are innocent and are likely to be found as such, the fact that the investigation is taking place makes things difficult for them. The process is inevitably conducted through newspaper columns because it is news, albeit of the worst sort. The situation can be particularly hard in cases such as the one mentioned by the hon. Member for Surrey Heath, where someone is standing for election. Understandably, people will ask whether they should be standing for election as they are under investigation.</p><p>
